ğŸ§  Logic: JPA (Java Persistence API) is the specification for persisting (storing) Java objects into a relational database. It is the standard interface defined by Java.Hibernate is the most popular $\mathbf{implementation}$ of the JPA specification. It is an ORM (Object-Relational Mapping) tool that bridges the gap between the object-oriented Java world and the relational database world.Goal: Eliminate the need for writing repetitive SQL and manual JDBC code. Hibernate maps Java classes (entities) to database tables, and Java object fields to table columns.ğŸ“Œ Example (JPA Annotation):Java// Marks the Java class as a table (Entity)
@Entity 
// Defines the primary key
@Id 
// Defines the column name for the field
@Column(name = "user_name") 
private String name; 

// Methods like session.save(userObject) automatically generate INSERT statements.
